              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13674508660512521133">Quirky, witty read<br/><br/>The characters in this story are the types of characters young adults will truly love. They are funny, adventurous, and witty. The way he wrote in such detail about each character really help the story flow from page to page, by the end of the first chapter Melody and Flutter were my favorites<br/><br/>Melody Jackson family and her tries to be your average day family admist of life&apos;s little adventures. But once her father starts telling stories, who knows what is going to go through Melo</span>
  <span id="freeText13674508660512521133" style="display:none">Quirky, witty read<br /><br />The characters in this story are the types of characters young adults will truly love. They are funny, adventurous, and witty. The way he wrote in such detail about each character really help the story flow from page to page, by the end of the first chapter Melody and Flutter were my favorites<br /><br />Melody Jackson family and her tries to be your average day family admist of life's little adventures. But once her father starts telling stories, who knows what is going to go through Melody's head.<br /><br />I would recommend this book to anyone who enjoys a quirky, witty, young adult read. One that well keep you turning the pages to the end.<br /><br />Reviewed by Stacie at Double Decker Books</span>
