<div id="review_1155669273" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1155669273" />
    <a title="Lori Johnson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15153264-lori-johnson"><img alt="Lori Johnson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1354595902p2/15153264.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1155669273?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lori Johnson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lori Johnson" href="/user/show/15153264-lori-johnson">Lori Johnson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Young adults and adults</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Lori by: </span>
      Author
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15153264-lori-johnson?shelf=1-first-reads">1-first-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15153264-lori-johnson?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1155669273" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5100156828330963900">I received this ARC book from the author through GoodReads First Reads in an electronic form. This story is a playful and imaginative romp through childhood and adulthood imaginations. B.M.B. Johnson (no relation to this reviewer) cleverly takes you through the emotions of making a new friend and the hurdles and rewards of that experience. The Melody and Flutter characters are clearly developed into those that seem to welcome you into their world as if you are one of the neighborhood children wh</span>
  <span id="freeText5100156828330963900" style="display:none">I received this ARC book from the author through GoodReads First Reads in an electronic form. This story is a playful and imaginative romp through childhood and adulthood imaginations. B.M.B. Johnson (no relation to this reviewer) cleverly takes you through the emotions of making a new friend and the hurdles and rewards of that experience. The Melody and Flutter characters are clearly developed into those that seem to welcome you into their world as if you are one of the neighborhood children who play together regularly. The parents are intelligent, playful, resourceful and engaging. The villains are menacing and dangerous without any overtly horror that, in a lot of young adult books is typically gratuitous and unnecessary. B.M.B. Johnson has the experience, skill and vocabulary to describe the scary scenes without the unnecessary horror other authors lazily rely on. He also uses this same experience, skill and vocabulary to remind me of my childhood adventures and imagination that I very much enjoyed re-visiting through the delightful characters in "Melody Jackson and the House on Lafayette Street". I recommend this book and the others in the series to all ages and anyone who wants to revisit their childhood for a romp in their imagination!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5100156828330963900" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


