  <span id="freeText17507732911571851023" style="display:none">I received a free copy of this book for an honest review.<br /><br />This was a great book. When I first started reading the book, I thought it was more of a coming of age book, then when they approach the House on Lafayette Street, I thought it was going to be more of a thriller/ghost story. To have it end up being more sci-fi.<br /><br />The story didn't rely on one element. There were so many. There was the dynamic of the 2 girls, the quirky family, and to not give a way too much, all the other characters.<br /><br />I had a lot of fun reading this.</span>
